messages.content: What are the products are commercially produced using crickets?

As of July 16, 2025, the market for commercially produced cricket-based food products is experiencing significant growth, driven by increasing consumer demand for sustainable and alternative protein sources [marketgrowthreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [datainsightsmarket](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1]. The overall insect protein market is estimated to be valued at USD 1.89 billion in 2025 and is expected to reach USD 14.13 billion by 2032 [coherentmi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).

Here are some of the commercially available products:

*   **Cricket Flour:** Made from ground crickets, it is used in various food products like protein bars, snacks, baked goods, and pasta [coherentmi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [news-medical](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [lifecrosstraining](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [huhuly](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8).
*   **Cricket Protein Powder:** A concentrated source of protein from crickets, used in sports nutrition and dietary supplements [persistencemarketresearch](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [valuates](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6) [coherentmi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [huhuly](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8).
*   **Cricket Protein Bars and Snacks:** Convenient and protein-rich options [coherentmi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [datainsightsmarket](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [persistencemarketresearch](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2]. Cricket protein bars offer a compelling combination of nutrition, sustainability, and convenience [etprotein](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Whole Frozen Crickets:** Used in animal feed and, increasingly, in human food [datainsightsmarket](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1].
*   **Cricket-Enriched Bread:** Being explored as a solution for enhancing food security [flyingfoodproject](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10].
*   **Cricket Pasta:** Cricket pasta can be prepared by substituting some of the flour for cricket powder [3cricketeers](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18].
*   **Cricket snack mixes:** are available in various flavors like BBQ, chili-lime, and taco [3cricketeers](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-17].

Several companies are involved in the production of these products, including All Things Bugs, Entomo Farms, Aspire Food Group, Chapul, Exo, Cricket Flours, Protix, Bitty Foods, Chirps Chips, Cricket One, and Bug Farm Foods [lifecrosstraining](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [marketgrowthreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [valuates](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6) [coherentmi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [datainsightsmarket](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [agroreality](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [foodtimes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11) [thebugfarm](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12).
